bug.short_desc: Firefox: firefox.desktop file has encoding problem in some languages
bug.cf_doc_type: If docs needed, set a value

long_desc.thetext:
Created attachment 1206483 Screenshots of dash and firefox.desktop file
There is a soft hyphen encoding before the "New Window" desktop action in some languages, like in French.
See the screenshots with what it looks like in gnome-shell and the wrong content in /usr/share/applications/firefox.desktop itself.
The firefox.desktop file needs to be cleaned up.
Thanks for the report, could you please paste the right character and phrase there? Thank you.

Still on Fedora 25 :
­Nouvelle fenêtre
Should be:
Nouvelle fenêtre
The same problem is for Italian [it], as reported in bug https://bugzilla.redhat.com/show_bug.cgi?id=1400531, and apparently for [de], i.e. "­Neues Fenster" instead of "Neues Fenster".
I hope it is resolved now, please do not hesitate to reopen if you find otherwise.
